description:
AB2D R4 (v2) Data Dictionary

The AB2D Data Dictionary provides a detailed break-down of the claims data provided by the AB2D API. AB2D shares data according to R4 and STU3 versions of the FHIR standard. FHIR R4 is available using v2 of AB2D while FHIR STU3 can be accessed via AB2D v1. Both are covered in the AB2D Data Dictionary.

A downloadable version of the Data Dictionary is available.

definitions.field_description: This is the unique identification number for the claim.
An identifier which ties families of claims together (from resubmissions).

The unique CCW identifier for a beneficiary. The CCW assigns a unique beneficiary identification number to each individual who receives Medicare and/or Medicaid and uses that number to identify an individual’s records in all CCW data files. This number does not change during a beneficiary’s lifetime, and CCW uses each number only once. The BENE_ID is specific to the CCW and is not applicable to any other identification system or data source

Field provides a reference to the Patient endpoint FHIR Resource so that this beneficiaries patient data can be pulled down using the reference id (beneficiaryId). The value will look something like this: "Patient/123456".
Each resource has an id element which contains the "logical id" of the resource assigned by the server responsible for storing it.
A FHIR Identifier used to specify the FHIR Resource Type.

definitions.field_description: The date that this record was last updated within the database.

An assertion that the content within the FHIR resource response conforms to a FHIR resource profile defined by HL7 or other FHIR Accelerator Groups.  The industry standard profile that is used as a template for this FHIR Resource.
A Medicare Beneficiary Identifier (MBI) assigned to a beneficiary.  This particular (MBI) is the most recent/current identifier assigned to the beneficiary.

Indicator to demonstrate if a claim is still 'active' or not ('cancelled'). Final action records are only indicative of the latest accepted record within a claim family that has been linked by the Medicare Advantage Organization (MAO) and may not be indicative of risk-adjustment eligibility.

The first day on the billing statement covering services rendered to the beneficiary (a.k.a. 'Statement Covers From Date').
The last day on the billing statement covering services rendered to the beneficiary (a.k.a. 'Statement Covers Thru Date').
